{"_id":"4b976270-e5e7-4ba9-a948-58abdb3bcc1d","type":"ability","name":"Push Through","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/athletics.svg","system":{"skill":"Athletics","name":"Push Through","rank":"3","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"1","description":"At any time during your turn, you can spend 1 Vigour to ignore the effects of the Dazed, Weakened, Slowed, Burning, Charged, and Corroding conditions until the end of your next turn. If you spend 2 Vigour instead, you also ignore all penalties from stat burn.","domain":"Physical","costtype":"vigour","skill_id":"athletics"}}
{"_id":"5f587ff9-956f-4b39-9be0-7a72250b1905","type":"ability","name":"Wrestler","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/athletics.svg","system":{"skill":"Athletics","name":"Wrestler","rank":"3","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"","description":"You may use the Hold unarmed technique with your athletics skill.","domain":"Physical","costtype":"","skill_id":"athletics"}}
{"_id":"7d0c30b3-4701-4759-a807-35feb2247696","type":"ability","name":"Second Wind","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/athletics.svg","system":{"skill":"Athletics","name":"Second Wind","rank":"3","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"","description":"Once per day, when using Catch Your Breath to heal, you can treat this as a rest instead. You do not lose Endurance during this rest.","domain":"Physical","costtype":"","skill_id":"athletics"}}
{"_id":"ac6cc61b-4dec-462b-9322-d5ac73e295aa","type":"ability","name":"Feats of Strength","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/athletics.svg","system":{"skill":"Athletics","name":"Feats of Strength","rank":"5","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"1 Minute","cost":"3","description":"You can perform incredible feats of strength. When you use this ability, your physical prowess is improved beyond the natural for up to a minute. You gain a boon to Athletics checks, and can do things impossible to normal people, such as breaking through stone walls with your bare fists, throwing person-sized objects dozens of meters, or lifting an autocart over your head. Once during the course of this time, you gain an Epic Boon on a strength-based check.","domain":"Physical","costtype":"vigour","skill_id":"athletics"}}
{"_id":"db519be9-8df2-46ee-8792-db241107c0bd","type":"ability","name":"Boxer","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/athletics.svg","system":{"skill":"Athletics","name":"Boxer","rank":"1","type":"technique","action":"medium","defense":"agility","target":"Single","range":"Adjacent","duration":"","cost":"","description":"You use the Athletics skill to make an unarmed attack. This is treated as a weapon attack with Medium speed that deals Light damage. These attacks can be made even when your hands are occupied by using your feet, head, or whole body.","domain":"Physical","costtype":"","skill_id":"athletics"}}
{"_id":"df5a367c-84ab-44ba-95f2-a111172e153b","type":"ability","name":"Distance Runner","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/athletics.svg","system":{"skill":"Athletics","name":"Distance Runner","rank":"1","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"1 Hour","cost":"1","description":"For the next hour, you do not tire from moving long distances carrying normal amounts of gear. You gain a boon on all checks made to move quickly over long distances. If the GM determines that your travel would cause you to burn Strength, you may use this ability to negate that burn.","domain":"Physical","costtype":"vigour","skill_id":"athletics"}}
{"_id":"ed8dab2c-01aa-47a7-a109-709ce2205d17","type":"ability","name":"Robust","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/athletics.svg","system":{"skill":"Athletics","name":"Robust","rank":"5","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"","description":"Whenever you would take a Major Wound, you may roll a d4. On a 3, you instead take a Minor Wound if possible. On a 4, the Major Wound is ignored altogether.","domain":"Physical","costtype":"","skill_id":"athletics"}}
